<p>
A <a href="/docs/Fields">field</a> implementing the Date & Time <a href="/docs/Field_Types">field type</a> can store a value as string that conforms to the format <code>YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS</code>. This format is preferred over others as lexicographical sorting has the same outcome as chronological sorting.
</p>

<p>
The Date & Time <a href="/docs/Field Type">Field Type</a> has two optional parameters named "Earliest" and "Latest" that can be used to specify the acceptable range of date times. If you need to store times in another format, use a <a href="/docs/Text_Field">Text Field</a>.
</p>

<div class="heading">Example Field</div>
<pre>{
	"Name" : "My Date & Time Field",
	"Field Type" : "Date & Time",
	"Description" : "The example usage of the Date & Time Field Type.",
	"Required" : true,
	"Parameters" : {
		"Earliest" : "1990-01-01 00:00:00",//OPTIONAL
		"Latest" : "1999-12-31 23:59:59"//OPTIONAL
	} 
}</pre>

<div class="heading">Example Value</div>
<pre>"ExampleUser.MyType.1" : {
	...
	"My Date & Time Field" : "1975-01-27 13:45:27",
	...
}</pre>